			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I think the biggest problem with the events in NRo and WC were the fact that higher lvl players were killing main mob just way too fast. I am on luclin server and in NRo. I play a lvl 13 wood elf rogue that is using banded cloak. There is/was a very nice cloak that drops/dropped in NRo for rogue. The event began and 2 minutes later the priest was killed and less than 12 minutes later the snake was killed and event ended. This was just plain rude as far as I am concerned. There were alot of lower lvl players that were looking for items to replace what they had. I think loot code isnt really the solution but it would have been nice to see the event last a specific amount of time w/out main mob being wiped out so quickly.<BR>
<BR>
The so called KSing was mainly due to lag issues. Many times I didnt see a mob being attacked until I was almost on top of it and had already hit it with a throwing knife. At that point I say sorry and go on my merry way, but I had alot of cases where I was fighting a mob and someone came up and just started slapping it and thus got more damage than i did and loooted w/out a word. These events did bring about some good but at the same time there were a whole lot of rude people out there. I honestly was glad to see the zone repop before main mob could be killed last night just because it was the same group that kept killing main mob all day and then they were complaining....LOL How Ironic huh
				</font>
