	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Now i may get flamed for this, but after attending these events, and reading a lot of posts, i think that the main problem with these events was that the loot was TOO GOOD.  For a while i thought trivial loot code was the answere, but reading mr anonymys post a few lines down, i agree with him.  A lvl 45 has worked hard to get where he is.  It would be ridiculous if a lvl 8 could go out and get better items than him because he is a high lvl.  If your going to make the loot so good (and it really was great.  I got items that were way better than anything i had) you have to give everyone equal acces to it.  If you did trivial loot, a high lvl would have to engage in much tougher, longer battles to get the same items that the lvl 8 got in 2 minutes.  And the high lvls would have longer down times in between their battles and would risk losing a LOT more exp.<BR>
<BR>
When you make an event where very high end equipment drops off of low lvl mobs, then of course your going to have high lvls killing those mobs.  they want to improve their gear just like the rest of us.  And lets be honest, how many of us low-mid lvl people were really at these events to gain exp?  If you wanted to gain exp, it was a great time to go to other zones like oasis and blackburrow because they were not nearly as crowded as usuall.  No, we lower lvl folk were just as loot hungry as the high lvls that are getting flamed.<BR>
<BR>
So, that said, the only way i see of fixing these events for next time is to make the quality of the loot at least somewhat proportional to the lvl of the mob.  The loot can still be better than normal (not to mention unique), but if I (a lvl 20 necro) can get *a ring with 3 int, 3ac, and 30 mana   *a cloak with 4 int, agi, dex   *a bracer with 4 int, 15 mana, and resisits   and * a tomb with 5int and risists.  If i was able to get such great items at lvl 20, then the loot for this event was just too good.<BR>
<BR>
Uular<BR>
<BR>
heh, i can't believe i'm complaining that my loot was too good.  :)
				</font>
			</td>

