				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I agree with the trivial loot/coin idea for events.  It certainly would have made this event more fun.  In the general case, I don't like trivial loot...but here everything was no drop.  I do agree that coins would allow you to make the rewards more level specific, and the high level players wouldnt feel neglected since they were getting better drops in their high level zone anyway.  But it is dangerous to assume that all high level chars would be more interested in the stuff dropping in the high level zone.  In this case everything was no drop, and high level players in EK were there for a reason.  That was not to sell loot locations (although this did occur to a degree), but to discover what was there and to hopefully improve their gear.  That privlege was earned by gaining their levels.  I hope that one day if I reach those kinds of levels, I will be able to walz into an event like this and start kicking tail like a demi-god.  Isnt that why you want to level in the first place?<BR>
