	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I think trivial loot MIGHT have worked for this event, but would have been very unfair to the higher level players.  If I had been a 46 bard unable to get a flameweaver because I had to stick to a zone where a 500dd AOE was killing people left and right, while some 8th level bard was running around without killing a thing in EK how would that have made me feel?  <BR>
<BR>
Should lower level characters be given an advantage over folks who have played the game longer?  There is nothing fair about that!  You already saw posts from players who felt this event diminished the efforts that they made to achieve lesser items.  How do you think those people would have felt if they were shut out from even participating for the gear that is better than their own, without placing their characters in extreme danger.<BR>
<BR>
I don't think you can define KS in a zone with over 200 people.  It was impossible to see far enough to know that something was engaged.  From personal experience, I benefited from higher level people in the zone, because they would kill something, and if they could not use the item they would often call out the location for someone else.  Trivial loot would have separated the players more by level, but it would not have been fair.  <BR>
<BR>
IF the best items only dropped in the high level zone, then maybe I see a case.  But how is it fair that a lvl 8 and a lvl 46 both compete for the SAME item with relatively the SAME effort.  doesnt that diminish the advantage of being level 46?  and if the lvl 8 dies in the attempt, regaining his lost experience will be trivial.  while the level 46 will require a great deal longer to recover his loss.<BR>
<BR>
If events like this have trivial loot, then i would like to see the loot be comparable to the best items achievable for that level range.  A drop like flameweaver would then not drop in a zone where a level 8 could easily get it, since it is somewhere among the top 6 weapons a bard can own in the game today.  <BR>
<BR>
trivial loot events might be fun if you want to gear a particular event to a certain level range.  This was the first time, in my experience, that I have seen this scale of a GM event.  Apparently the different zones were set up so that different level ranges could all participate.  There would be little incentive for a 45 to go to qeynos hills, because the chance of something nice dropping there was slim to none.  Unfortunately EK became the one size fits all zone of the event.<BR>
<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
